Iraqi leaders, fearing a U.S. air attack, distributed automatic weapons to tens of thousands  of its citizens, prepared to evacuate Baghdad's 4 million people to outlying camps and  ordered the formation of 11 new army divisions.
Japan and Europe joined the embargo  of Iraqi oil.
Reportedly, Kuwait's oil export facilities have been shut down.
It is  doubtful that Saudi Arabia will make up the shortage.
Saddam Hussein said Iraq is  withdrawing its forces from Kuwait.
President Bush said he is lying.
Iraqi troops massed  along the Kuwait-Saudi border are digging in but there is no indication they are preparing  to invade.  
